This paper deals with natural language processing and information extraction from tweets, which are short, noisy, and context-dependent. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of named entity recognition and disambiguation, which are common techniques in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Information Science (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art systems, which suggests a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
